OL,3,CGovernment proposes higher minimum
OL,4,Cwage from next April
OL,6,FWorkers in Jersey on the minimum wage
OL,7,Fcould soon be paid more.
OL,9,FThat is after the Social Security
OL,10,FMinister set out plans to raise their
OL,11,Fhourly salary by 4.5% from #13 to
OL,12,F#13.59.
OL,14,FThe proposed change would be
OL,15,Fintroduced from 1 April 2026 and is
OL,16,Fbeing announced now so that employers
OL,17,Fhave time to prepare.
