OL,3,CGovernment proposes higher minimum
OL,4,Cwage from next April
OL,6,FIf brought in, it would fulfil the
OL,7,FGovernment's pledge to raise the
OL,8,Fminimum wage to two-thirds of the
OL,9,Fisland's average salary - which latest
OL,10,Ffigures show is #20.33 per hour.
OL,12,FJersey's Social Security Minister,
OL,13,FDeputy Lyndsay Feltham, says: "This
OL,14,Fproposed increase is another important
OL,15,Fstep in ensuring that employees are
OL,16,Fpaid fairly in Jersey.
OL,18,F"I would like to encourage employers
OL,19,Fto go further and seek voluntary
OL,20,Faccreditation with the Living Wage
OL,21,FFoundation, through Caritas Jersey."
