OL,3,CGovernment proposes higher minimum
OL,4,Cwage from next April
OL,6,FThe living wage currently stands at
OL,7,F#14.13 per hour.
OL,9,FDeputy Feltham also references the
OL,10,Ftrainee minimum wage, which had been
OL,11,Fabolished at the start of the year and
OL,12,Fthen reintroduced in September after
OL,13,Fbusinesses reported struggling to
OL,14,Fafford the higher staff costs.
OL,16,FShe adds: "I have maintained the
OL,17,Ftrainee rate at #10.50 next year,
OL,18,Fensuring that those starting a new
OL,19,Fcareer are able to find an
OL,20,Fapprenticeship or trainee scheme to
OL,21,Fhelp them develop their skills."
